On Wed, Jul 10, 2002 at 01:46:22PM +0000, Mikhael Goikhman wrote:
> On 09 Jul 2002 08:18:33 +0200, Olivier Chapuis wrote:
> We already changed the colorset syntax by removing FvwmTheme.
> I suggest to use the word Image for the same reason that we once renamed
> PixmapPath to ImagePath, now fvwm even supports xbm and png, not just xpm.

PixmapPath was *not* renamed to ImagePath.  The reason for the new
name was to merge the two separate paths (IconPath and PixmapPath)
into a single one.

Pixmap is the name of the internal X picture object, not the name
of the image file format.  Whatever the image is loaded from, X
still uses Pixmaps internally.  I see no naming conflict here. 

