This is probably started after the rxvt/aterm copying workaround commit.
Regardless of whether this is related or not, I think rxvt bugs are better
to be fixed in rxvt, not in fvwm, it is not a closed product.

I can always reproduce this with no config (MouseFocus) or SloppyFocus.
Place 2 xterms or rxvts like this:

           _________ 
          |         |
          |         |
    ______|         |
   |   abc|    B    |
   |      |         |
   |      |_________|
   |    A    |
   |         |
   |_________|

or this:

           _________
          |         |
          |         |
   _______|__       |
   |   abcde | B    |
   |         |      |
   |         |______|
   |    A    |
   |         |
   |_________|

Now, Raise/Lower B several times (for this bug to work it is important
that B is the last dealt window before you start copying in A).
Using mouse button 1, copy text "abc" and continue with a pointer to the
right, so it ends up in B. Release the mouse button. B is not focused.
